The paper discusses a programming language model and its properties, which suggests it belongs to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The model is synchronous and involves threads, which also suggests it could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper discusses determinism and computational expressivity, which are topics related to Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses program equivalence, which is a topic related to Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category.
